### HYMN LXIX

#### A priest's prayer for power and glory

<span class="margnote"><span id="an_0606901">1</span></span>Mine be the
glory in the hill, in vales, in cattle, and in gold,  
  Mine be the sweetness that is found in nectar and in flowing  
   wine!  
<span class="margnote"><span id="an_0606902">2</span></span>With your
delicious honey balm me, Asvins, Lords of splendid  
   light!  
  That clear and resonant may be the voice I utter to mankind.  
<span class="margnote"><span id="an_0606903">3</span></span>In me be
strength, in me be fame, in me the power of sacrifice:  
  Prajāpati establish this in me as firm as light in heaven!

